subSubSection.paragraph:
Aptostichus simus
is generally abundant at some localities along the California coast but has been almost entirely extirpated from many beaches in Southern California. For example, the species is very rare at the type locality, Silver Strand State Beach. Moreover, the species is particularly vulnerable to invasive plant species (e.g., ice plant, 
Carpobrotus edulis
) and is highly structured genetically across its distribution thus many populations contain unique alleles (
Bond et al. 2001
). Consequently, I would consider this species to be vulnerable or imperiled due to its low abundance at many localities and extreme structuring.
